er Vision task. Just  Note that Pytorch operates with Dynamic Graph (The weight-value graph of the whole process is remade every epoch). Torchvision library is useful in image preprocessing. Transforms.Compose helps in conversion of image pixels to float as well as other augmentation like Clahe and Jitters. torch.utils.data gives us Dataset, that helps us to prepare our dataset in a class as they run typical functions like __len__ and __getitem__ , and DataLoader that finally prepares our train_loader and test_loader </p>\n","<h6>Note: ALWAYS CHECK FILE NAMES BEFORE USING</h6>"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":1,"id":"773456b0","metadata":{"_cell_guid":"033a9950-6d13-4697-b187-f488b91dbcf7","_uuid":"fc802d17-2978-45cf-9f5e-8bfd26210903","collapsed":false,"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-21T14:38:21.033871Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-21T14:38:21.033209Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.731505Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.730666Z"},"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"papermill":{"duration":45.711338,"end_time":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.733439+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-21T14:38:21.022101+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[],"source":["%%capture\n","import os\n","! pip install scikit-learn numpy matplotlib pandas lightning torch timm==0.5.4\n","import torch\n","import torch.nn as nn\n","import torch.nn.functional as F\n","from torch.optim import Adam\n","import lightning as L\n","from torchvision import datasets, transforms\n","import numpy as np\n","from glob import glob\n","from PIL import Image\n","import logging\n","from torch.utils.data import Dataset, DataLoader\n","import torchvision.transforms as transforms"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"4f92eeba","metadata":{"_cell_guid":"73cecda1-ea82-4c94-b1bf-7cf4dd7d8fc8","_uuid":"b6990468-67a4-455e-8c76-a1c038aa358e","collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"papermill":{"duration":0.009862,"end_time":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.753902+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.74404+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["### Declare the transforms\n","<p>Declare the transforms.Compose because we will use this to convert our image to float type</p>"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":2,"id":"f3cb29ab","metadata":{"_cell_guid":"0ab6d2c7-89ea-4f1c-894c-59cefbfb1b11","_uuid":"17b3065d-6264-4a8d-a702-fb64167d0329","collapsed":false,"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.775102Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.774668Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.778498Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.777917Z"},"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"papermill":{"duration":0.015831,"end_time":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.779817+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.763986+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[],"source":["transform=transforms.Compose([transforms.ToTensor(),])"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"50869907","metadata":{"_cell_guid":"9c1a45a3-8f2b-456c-b8d6-e80f55ae6239","_uuid":"0dcfe19b-43e3-4833-9ce3-24d394685dc9","collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"papermill":{"duration":0.010208,"end_time":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.799776+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.789568+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["### Class dataset\n","<p> Build the Class and invoke the function Dataset from torch.utils.data so that it upload the input and prepares the data for train and test later. We extract image from file, strip and split the file name to get class name and get the corresponding attribute matrix after we have a class to index map. The class is the label index in order as given. Then we return the image, label and respective attribute side by side</p>\n","<h6>NB: Check the file-paths everytime you copy-paste this block</h6>"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":3,"id":"8ec2a1a3","metadata":{"_cell_guid":"ba5bc911-e49b-4dc9-9406-52092b860f76","_uuid":"617e4a77-4427-4964-af1f-5ffb621af960","collapsed":false,"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.821124Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.820875Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.827687Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.827125Z"},"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"papermill":{"duration":0.019216,"end_time":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.828893+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.809677+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[],"source":["class AnimalDataset(Dataset):\n","    def __init__(self, classes_file_path, transform=None):\n","        self.transform = transform\n","        # 50x85 /kaggle/input/datasets/rrebirrth/animals-with-attributes-2\n","        self.predicate_binary_mat = np.genfromtxt(\n","            '/kaggle/input/datasets/rrebirrth/animals-with-attributes-2/Animals_with_Attributes2/predicate-matrix-binary.txt',\n","            dtype='int'\n","        )\n","        self.class_to_index = {}\n","        with open('/kaggle/input/datasets/rrebirrth/animals-with-attributes-2/Animals_with_Attributes2/classes.txt') as f:\n","            for idx, line in enumerate(f):\n","                class_name = line.strip().split('\\t')[1]\n","                self.class_to_index[class_name] = idx\n","        self.img_paths = []\n","        self.img_class_indices = [] \n","        self.img_attr_vectors = []  \n","        with open(classes_file_path) as f:\n","            selected_classes = [line.strip() for line in f]\n","        for class_name in selected_classes:\n","            class_index = self.class_to_index[class_name]\n","            class_attr = self.predicate_binary_mat[class_index]\n","            folder_path = os.path.join(\n","                '/kaggle/input/datasets/rrebirrth/animals-with-attributes-2/Animals_with_Attributes2/JPEGImages',\n","                class_name\n","            )\n","            for img_path in glob(os.path.join(folder_path, '*.jpg')):\n","                self.img_paths.append(img_path)\n","                self.img_class_indices.append(class_index)\n","                self.img_attr_vectors.append(class_attr)\n","    def __len__(self):\n","        return len(self.img_paths)\n","    def __getitem__(self, idx):\n","        img_path = self.img_paths[idx]\n","        image = Image.open(img_path).convert('RGB')\n","        if self.transform:\n","            image = self.transform(image)\n","        attr_vector = torch.tensor(self.img_attr_vectors[idx], dtype=torch.float32)\n","        class_index = self.img_class_indices[idx]  # true label\n","        return image, attr_vector, class_index, img_path"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"6b666bd3","metadata":{"_cell_guid":"324fd26b-3c5c-4ea1-b886-70a332ec15f9","_uuid":"eab3a2b1-1e20-4dbd-8368-5bd7292f51f7","collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"papermill":{"duration":0.009776,"end_time":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.848686+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.83891+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["### Prepare loaders\n","<p>Perform some augmentation and prepare the train_loader and test_loader here</p>"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":4,"id":"89865836","metadata":{"_cell_guid":"3e302292-2ce2-47c1-8221-e163dbd53197","_uuid":"91082cbd-cfd0-41e3-9f24-9fc35dbf9645","collapsed":false,"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.869511Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.869107Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.873901Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.873296Z"},"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"papermill":{"duration":0.016664,"end_time":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.875098+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.858434+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[],"source":["def get_data_loaders(train_classes_file, test_classes_file, batch_size=16):\n","    train_transform = transforms.Compose([\n","        transforms.RandomRotation(15),\n","        transforms.RandomHorizontalFlip(),\n","        transforms.ColorJitter(brightness=0.3, contrast=0.3),\n","        transforms.Resize((224, 224)),\n","        transforms.ToTensor()\n","    ])\n","\n","    test_transform = transforms.Compose([\n","        transforms.Resize((224, 224)),\n","        transforms.ToTensor()\n","    ])\n","\n","    train_dataset = AnimalDataset(train_classes_file, transform=train_transform)\n","    test_dataset = AnimalDataset(test_classes_file, transform=test_transform)\n","\n","    train_loader = DataLoader(train_dataset, batch_size=batch_size, shuffle=True, num_workers=4)\n","    test_loader = DataLoader(test_dataset, batch_size=batch_size, shuffle=False, num_workers=4)\n","\n","    return train_loader, test_loader"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"914a1a1d","metadata":{"_cell_guid":"099f9ac2-f4de-4dd3-9d20-7f1cea90ac27","_uuid":"24907b63-6fe4-450e-a360-d284e826b85e","collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"papermill":{"duration":0.009744,"end_time":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.894751+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.885007+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["### Use loader to build the final loader\n","<p>Use the above function and file name to upload the final train and test loader</p>\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":5,"id":"46a93a62","metadata":{"_cell_guid":"ec7954f8-b742-46f3-99ca-80636e7bf007","_uuid":"490aa9d6-345b-41f8-b3f5-038323a434ee","collapsed":false,"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.916687Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.916283Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-21T14:39:08.261656Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-21T14:39:08.261021Z"},"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false},"papermill":{"duration":1.358383,"end_time":"2026-04-21T14:39:08.26329+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-21T14:39:06.904907+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[],"source":["train_loader, test_loader = get_data_loaders(\n","    '/kaggle/input/datasets/rrebirrth/animals-with-attributes-2/Animals_wi